steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"4vh4i","text":"To measure cytosolic calcium, 5 uM Fura-2 or Fluo-4 was added to cells at room temperature for 40 minutes made up in HBSS (Invitrogen).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"71cf4","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6c0un","text":"To measure mitochondrial calcium, cells were incubated with 2μM X-Rhod-1 in HBSS for 40 minutes. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"abtqs","text":"Cells are then washed 2x in HBSS at room temperature. They are now ready for imaging.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"e022v","text":"All probes are from Molecular Probes (Thermo Fisher Scientific). Fura-2-AM is a ratiometric dye with a high affinity for Ca2+. It is used to measure [Ca2+]c.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4mvog","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"feg4k","text":"Fluo-4-AM is a calcium indicator.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6cpn5","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3kpn5","text":"X-Rhod-1-AM is a calcium indicator which localises to mitochondria.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bjc3e","text":"[Ca2+]c is monitored in cells by obtaining the ratio between the excitation at 340 nm (high Ca2+) and 380 nm (low Ca2+) for which fluorescence light was reflected through a 515 nm long pass filter. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bd08d","text":"The cells were excited sequentially at 340 and 380nm using light from a Xenon arc lamp. A time-series with 1 or 5 second intervals was performed to establish basal fluorescence before 50mM KCl was added to depolarise the membrane.The emitted fluorescence was measured at 515 nm on a cooled camera device (CCD).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6kq40","text":"[Ca2+]c  using Fura-2 AM was also imaged on a Nikon Ti2 inverted microscope with Perfect Focus System, an ASI motorised XY stage with piezo Z and an Okolab environmental chamber with a CO2 mixer. Imaged were acquired using an Andor iXon Ultra897 EMCCD camera. Cells were excited with a Cairn FuraLED light engine optimised for 340 and 380 nm with a dichroic mirror T400lp (Chroma) and an emission filter ET510/80m (Chroma), using a 40x 1.3 NA S Fluor objective. The microscope was controlled with Micro-Manager v2.0","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":3,"length":2},{"style":"sup","offset":187,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":6,"length":3}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6of4","text":"Live-cell imaging was performed excited by a 488 nm laser and measured at 520 nm. A time-series with 5 second intervals was performed to establish basal fluorescence before 50mM KCl was added to depolarise the membrane and measure fluorescence intensity increase, and recovery. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6ljmm","text":"Live-cell imaging was performed excited by a 561 nm laser. A time-series with 5 second intervals was performed to establish basal fluorescence before 50mM KCl was added to depolarise the membrane and measure fluorescence intensity increase, and recovery giving readouts for mitochondrial calcium.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
